  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'How do mushroom gummies support brain health?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Lion\'s mane mushroom (Hericium erinaceus) is the primary brain-supporting mushroom, containing two unique compound classes: hericenones (found in the fruiting body) and erinacines (found in the mycelium). These compounds stimulate the production of Nerve Growth Factor (NGF) — a protein essential for the growth, maintenance, and survival of neurons. NGF promotes neurogenesis (the creation of new neurons), supports myelination (the protective coating around nerve fibers that enables fast signal transmission), and protects existing neurons from damage. Clinical trials in older adults with mild cognitive impairment showed that lion\'s mane supplementation (3g/day for 16 weeks) significantly improved cognitive function scores compared to placebo. Other brain-supporting mushrooms include cordyceps (brain oxygen delivery), reishi (neuroprotection and sleep quality), and chaga (antioxidant neuroprotection).' } },
  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Which mushroom is best for brain focus?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Lion\'s mane is the best mushroom for brain focus and cognitive function. Its unique compounds (hericenones and erinacines) are the only known natural compounds that stimulate NGF production in the brain. For specific focus needs: (1) Lion\'s mane — best for overall cognitive function, memory, focus, and neuroprotection. (2) Cordyceps — best for mental energy and alertness through improved brain oxygen delivery and ATP production. (3) Lion\'s mane + cordyceps combination — provides both structural brain support (NGF) and energy-based mental clarity (ATP/oxygen). (4) Reishi — best for reducing brain fog caused by stress and poor sleep (calming, sleep-enhancing). For maximum focus benefits, look for lion\'s mane products made from fruiting body extract (contains hericenones) standardized to beta-glucan content of at least 20%, with at least 500mg per serving.' } },
  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'How long do mushroom brain gummies take to work?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The timeline depends on the mechanism: Acute effects (cordyceps): some users notice improved mental energy and alertness within 1-2 weeks, as cordyceps supports ATP production and brain oxygenation relatively quickly. Medium-term effects (lion\'s mane cognitive improvement): the clinical trial showing significant cognitive improvement used 16 weeks (4 months) of daily supplementation. NGF-stimulated neurogenesis and neural repair are biological processes that take time — expect 4-8 weeks for initial subtle improvements and 12-16 weeks for meaningful cognitive enhancement. Long-term effects (neuroprotection): the protective benefits of ongoing NGF stimulation and antioxidant neuroprotection accumulate over months and years of consistent supplementation. Commit to at least 8-12 weeks of daily use before evaluating brain-specific results. Use objective cognitive assessments (memory games, focus trackers) rather than subjective impression alone.' } },
  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Fruiting body vs. mycelium: which is better for brain?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'For brain-specific benefits, the answer is nuanced: Fruiting body extracts contain hericenones — compounds that stimulate NGF production and have the most clinical evidence for cognitive improvement. Fruiting body extracts also have higher beta-glucan content (the primary bioactive polysaccharide). Mycelium contains erinacines — a different class of NGF-stimulating compounds not found in fruiting bodies. Erinacines are smaller molecules that may cross the blood-brain barrier more readily than hericenones. The ideal brain supplement contains BOTH fruiting body and mycelium to access both hericenones and erinacines for maximum NGF stimulation. However, many mycelium products are grown on grain substrates and contain significant starch filler (up to 70% grain) that dilutes the actual mushroom content. Look for products that specify "fruiting body extract" with stated beta-glucan content, or full-spectrum products that include both fruiting body and mycelium with verified mushroom compound content.' } },
