    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Mushroom Gummies for Brain</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How do mushroom gummies support brain health?</summary><p>Lion's mane stimulates NGF (Nerve Growth Factor) via hericenones and erinacines — the only known natural compounds with this ability. NGF promotes neurogenesis, myelination, and neuroprotection. Clinical trial: 16 weeks of 3g/day improved cognitive function in mild cognitive impairment.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Which mushroom is best for brain focus?</summary><p>Lion's mane for structural support (NGF, memory, focus). Cordyceps for mental energy (ATP, oxygenation). Combination of both is ideal. For stress-related brain fog: add reishi. Look for fruiting body extract with 20%+ beta-glucans and at least 500mg per serving.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long do mushroom brain gummies take to work?</summary><p>Cordyceps energy: 1-2 weeks. Lion's mane cognitive improvement: 4-8 weeks initial, 12-16 weeks for significant benefits. Neuroprotection: accumulates over months/years. The clinical trial showed significance at 16 weeks. Commit to 8-12 weeks minimum. Track objectively.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Fruiting body vs. mycelium: which is better for brain?</summary><p>Fruiting body has hericenones (NGF) + higher beta-glucans. Mycelium has erinacines (different NGF compounds). Ideal: both. Concern: mycelium-on-grain products are 50-70% starch. Choose verified fruiting body extract or full-spectrum with beta-glucan testing.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take mushroom brain gummies with other nootropics?</summary><p>Yes. Good combinations: lion's mane + caffeine/L-theanine (structure + acute focus), lion's mane + omega-3 (neural growth + membrane health), lion's mane + bacopa (NGF + cholinergic memory). No known dangerous interactions with common nootropics.</p></details>

